<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 3:27PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of east central
Broadwater and south central Meagher Counties through 400 PM MDT...
At 327 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles south of White Sulphur Springs, moving northeast at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Ringling.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 12 between mile markers 23 and 39.
Highway 89 between mile markers 41 and 57.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
